The paper also discusses unobservable constructs and the need to infer them from observable properties, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on identifying and mitigating fairness-related harms suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the potential for mismatches between theoretical constructs and their operationalization, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the contested nature of fairness, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
